Kisii South Knut executive secretary Geoffrey Mogire is among 14 people nominated to be chief officers in the Kisii government. The list has been tabled in the county assembly for vetting. It was presented by majority leader Timothy Ogugu to the assemblyâ€™s committee on appointment. The team will vet them and present a report to the assembly, either recommending them for appointment or rejecting them.  The number of chief officer posts have been increased to 14 from nine in the previous government. Governor James Ongwae has dropped six of the nine chief officers who served in the last term.